    "Definition of multidrug-resistant bacteriaDefinitions and testing methods were used as described previously [37].",
    "MDR bacteria were defined according to the definitions of the Dutch Working Group on Infection Prevention [38].",
    "This includes ESBL-producing Enterobacterales; Enterobacterales and Acinetobacter spp.",
    "that are resistant to both fluoroquinolones and an aminoglycoside or produce carbapenemases; Pseudomonas aeruginosa that produces carbapenemase or is resistant to at least three of the following antibiotic classes or agents: fluoroquinolones, aminoglycosides, ceftazidime or piperacillin, and carbapenems; both penicillin and vancomycin-resistant Enterococcus faecium (VRE); or methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA).",
    "Culture and antimicrobial susceptibility testing of multidrug-resistant bacteriaTo identify MDR bacteria and calculate the prevalence among FMT donors and recipients, stool samples were selectively cultured as described previously [37]."
